    • Method Detail

      • parseAST

        public AbstractOperableSyntaxAST<?> parseAST(AbstractSyntaxAST parentAST,
                                             SyntaxAnalyzer syntaxAnalyzer)
        Description copied from class: AbstractSyntaxAST
        This method will be overwritten by the classes which extends AbstractSyntaxAST. It will return a AbstractSyntaxAST if everything worked correctly or null if an error occurred. The parent AbstractSyntaxAST is used to check if the AbstractSyntaxAST can be created inside it and the SyntaxAnalyzer is just used to check the syntax of current/next and peeked AbstractToken.
        Specified by:
        parseAST in class AbstractSyntaxAST
        Parameters:
        parentAST - the parent AbstractSyntaxAST which should get used to check if the AbstractSyntaxAST can be created inside it.
        syntaxAnalyzer - the SyntaxAnalyzer which is used for checking the syntax with methods like SyntaxAnalyzer.matchesCurrentToken(TokenType) or SyntaxAnalyzer.matchesNextToken(SymbolToken.SymbolType) )}.
        Returns:
        null if an error occurred or the parsed AbstractSyntaxAST if everything worked correctly.

      • printSyntaxAST

        public void printSyntaxAST(java.io.PrintStream printStream,
                           java.lang.String indents)
        Description copied from class: AbstractSyntaxAST
        This method will be overwritten by the classes which extends AbstractSyntaxAST. It will print with help of the PrintStream and indents a tree which is used for debugging. To print all RootSyntaxASTs you just need to call this method ArkoiCompiler.printSyntaxTree(PrintStream).
        Specified by:
        printSyntaxAST in class AbstractSyntaxAST
        Parameters:
        printStream - the PrintStream which should get used for the output.
        indents - the indents which will make the AST look like a Tree.
